data.title: Nominations and Resignations in 2023
data.text:
Titular Patriarchal See of Alexandria (Greek-Melkite Rite) was suppressed (Egypt)

Titular Episcopal See of Medininkai was restored (Lithuania)

Titular Patriarchal See of Jerusalem (Greek-Melkite Rite) was suppressed (Palestine)

Msgr. Tomislav ukez resigned as Person-in-charge of Central Statistics Office of the Church

Archbishop Luigi Roberto Cona, Apostolic Nuncio to El Salvador, was appointed as Extra-Regional Observer to Central American Integration System (SICA)

Fr. Giordano Piccinotti, S.D.B., was appointed as Member of Commission for Confidential Matters

Msgr. Marco Ganci, Priest of CatanzaroSquillace (Italy), Permanent Observer to Council of Europe and Prelate of Honour of His Holiness, was appointed as Observer to International Commission on Civil Status (ICCS)

Msgr. Gianpaolo Montini resigned as Secretary of Commission for Advocates

Fr. Luigi Maria Epicoco resigned as Ecclesiastical Assistant of Dicastery for Communication and Editorialist of LOsservatore Romano

Fr. Rafael Garca de la Serrana Villalobos resigned as President of Personnel Commission of Vatican City State

Mr. Antonino Intersimone, Director of Directorate of Telecommunications and Information Systems of Vatican City State, was appointed as President of Personnel Commission of Vatican City State

Msgr. Pawe Malecha, Priest of Pozna (Poland) and Prelate of Honour of His Holiness, was appointed as Secretary of Commission for Advocates

Archbishop Santiago De Wit Guzmn, Apostolic Nuncio to Antigua and Barbuda, Apostolic Nuncio to Belize, Apostolic Nuncio to Grenada, Apostolic Nuncio to Guyana, Apostolic Nuncio to Saint Kitts and Nevis, Apostolic Nuncio to Saint Vincent and Grenadines, Apostolic Nuncio to Suriname, Apostolic Nuncio to Trinidad and Tobago, Apostolic Delegate to Antilles, Apostolic Nuncio to Bahamas, Apostolic Nuncio to Barbados, Apostolic Nuncio to Dominica, Apostolic Nuncio to Jamaica and Apostolic Nuncio to Saint Lucia, was appointed as Plenipotentiary Representative to Caribbean Community (CARICOM)

Dr. Maximino Caballero Ledo, Prefect of Secretariat for the Economy, was appointed as Member of Commission for Confidential Matters

Patriarch Youssef Absi, resigned as Patriarch of Alexandria of the Greek-Melkites and Patriarch of Jerusalem of the Greek-Melkites

Fr. Jos Ferreira Filho, M.O., was appointed as Superior General of Missionaries of Workers

Fr. Jan Van Roy, M.O., resigned as Superior General of Missionaries of Workers

Msgr. Pierangelo Pietracatella, Priest of Tortona (Italy), Head of Office of Tribunal of the Roman Rota and Chaplain of His Holiness, was appointed as Prelate Auditor of Tribunal of the Roman Rota

Bishop Milan Lach, S.J., Bishop of Parma of the Ruthenians (USA), was appointed as Titular Bishop of Ostracine and Auxiliary Bishop of Bratislava of the Slovaks (Slovakia)

Archbishop Joseph Salvador Marino resigned as President of Pontifical Ecclesiastical Academy

Bishop Kurt Richard Burnette, Bishop of Passaic of the Ruthenians (USA) and Apostolic Administrator of Saints Cyril and Methodius of Toronto of the Ruthenians (Canada), was appointed as Apostolic Administrator of Parma of the Ruthenians (USA) and Apostolic Administrator of Holy Protection of Mary of Phoenix of the Ruthenians (USA)

Bishop Thomas James Olmsted resigned as Apostolic Administrator of Holy Protection of Mary of Phoenix of the Ruthenians (USA)
